blueprint.label: Train Rate Display
blueprint.description:
Connections via Power Pole:
  green: train detector outputs
  red: enable (checkmark=1)

Once enabled, lights will blink blue until 10 trains have passed.  After 10 trains, the clock will start, indicated by the yellow "second hand" moving around the outside..  After 10 minutes, the center ligts will go white to indicate a stable display.

As trains pass, the rate is updated in real time.  In addtion, the lights are color-coded:
  green: 30+ tpm
  cyan: 25-30 tpm
  red: 0-25 tpm
